## System Model Structure

Always start by reading the system model index:

```yaml
# .osk/system-model/index.yaml (~200 lines)
- Quick stats (components, data categories, actors)
- Section summaries
- Cross-references (which component handles which data)
- Compliance hints
```

Load additional sections as needed:
- `business.yaml` - Business context and processes
- `architecture.yaml` - Components and data flows
- `data.yaml` - Data inventory with classifications
- `actors.yaml` - Users, roles, service accounts
- `trust.yaml` - Trust zones and boundaries
- `integrations.yaml` - External integrations
- `security.yaml` - Existing security controls
- `gaps.yaml` - Discovery gaps

